<div style="color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #51b7cf; letter-spacing: 1px; word-spacing: 2px;">
<div class="reality-title">
{{Alt Class|ent=2|ext=3|env=2|no=983}}
'''Level 983''', also known as '''"Submechanophobia"''', is the '''984<sup>th</sup>''' level of '''[[The Backrooms]]'''.</div>

<div class="reality-title">
<span class="reality-title-main"><big><big><big>Description</big></big></big></span></div>
{{Blurimage|file=Submechanophobia.png|caption=A screenshot of a Submechanophobic. Photographer confirmed dead.}}Level 983 takes place in an old, decrepit theme park with no rides and contains a lot of water. The level's water seems to be an entire ocean and is speculated to be infinite. The park itself is an interior park, meaning the whole thing is inside, and it takes the place of what you'd typically see in a water-themed attraction in theme parks. However, this one looks a lot more abandoned, with wires hanging from the roof, lights occasionally flickering, wall textures peeling off, and ceiling tiles on the floor.


The main thing that makes this level different are entities known as "The Submechanophobics." They are old robots resembling sea creatures, and like the level, they also look old and decrepit. They are rather hostile and often sneak up on their victims before attacking. However, they can be outrun pretty easily, and some even just stay in the water.

Stations in this level are fairly uncommon and usually contain food from the Frontrooms. For example, you can easily find a popcorn station. There are also stations for items in the Backrooms themselves. (Ex. [[Almond Water]], [[Cashew Water]], and [[Moth Jelly]].) It is speculated that there are also stands for items exclusive to the level, but this has yet to be confirmed, as no one has come across one.
<div class="reality-title">
<span class="reality-title-main"><big><big><big>Entities</big></big></big></span></div>
===The Submechanophobics===
{{Blurimage|file=AlligatorRobot.jpg|caption=Another image of a Submechanophobic. Photographer status unknown.|width=200px}}These entities are the level's exclusive entities and are animatronics resembling creatures you'd find in swamps and deeper parts of the ocean. They are very hostile and tend to sneak up on their prey before attacking. [[Almond Water]] and [[Cashew Water]] work well as weapons against them, since splashing them with these liquids can cause them to malfunction and sometimes shut down outright. A wanderer once said that if you used [[Liquid Pain]] on them, they'd explode into a mess of nuts and bolts, but this has yet to be confirmed.



.....
<div class="reality-title">
<span class="reality-title-main"><big><big><big>Colonies & Outposts</big></big></big></span></div>
===The Ones Who Conquered Submechanophobics===
This group is filled with members who once had Submechanophobia, but managed to face the fear.
*8 Members.
*Friendly.
*Willing To Trade.
*Carries some [[Almond Water]] and [[Cashew Water]], which can be used to fight off against the Submechanophobics.
<div class="reality-title">
<span class="reality-title-main"><big><big><big>Entrances & Exits</big></big></big></span></div>
===Entrances===
*One can be warped to this level in any water-themed level when least expected
*Swimming into a pipe in [[Level 7]] will result in the wanderer coming out of the pipe into the level. The pipe will then cease to exist for you after you've entered the level using this exit.
*Noclip through an active sink in [[Level 570]] to teleport yourself here.
*Doing a backflip into the water in [[Level 7.1]] will result in you being sent here next to an Submechanophobic. '''It is highly advised to not use this entrance. Only use it if you brought some [[Almond Water]] or [[Cashew Water]].''' If not, then good luck, because you'll need it.
*Noclipping through a building in [[Level 428]] sends you here.

===Exits===
*It is rumored that killing all the agoraphobics could send you to any safe level that has an exit to [[The Frontrooms]], but this has yet to be confirmed.
*Trying to attack The Ones That Conquered Agoraphobia either sends you to [[Level !]], or [[You Cheated|they'll call it cheating.]]
*Swimming 100km leads you to [[The Void]]. '''Do not attempt this.'''
*Finding a set of doors and going out them will send you to [[Level 345]].
